locations = selectToList(db,"SELECT DISTINCT location from results")
locations = [l.split('--')[0] for l in locations]
locations = set(locations)
In [3]:
def loadData(step,location,browser,label):
    return selectToList(db,"""
        SELECT visualComplete85 FROM results WHERE step == """+str(step)+""" AND 
        location LIKE '%"""+location+"--"+browser+"""%' AND label LIKE '%"""+label+"""%';""")
In [4]:
for l in locations:
    boxes = []
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(0,l,"tor","original"),"Tor, No Ublock"))
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(0,l,"tor","Ublock"),"Tor, Ublock"))
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(0,l,"firefox","original"),"Firefox, No Ublock"))
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(0,l,"firefox","Ublock"),"Firefox, Ublock"))
    drawBoxes(boxes,'First Load 85% Visual Completion for '+regionToCity[l])
    
# These graphs show the time taken to load the majority of a web page 
# (judged according to its visual completition) after entering it into
# the url bar. I.E. without already having a connection open. 

# Figures are broken down by the browser used and whether Ublock was enabled.
In [5]:
for l in locations:
    boxes = []
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(1,l,"tor","original"),"Tor, No Ublock"))
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(1,l,"tor","Ublock"),"Tor, Ublock"))
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(1,l,"firefox","original"),"Firefox, No Ublock"))
    boxes.append(listToBox(loadData(1,l,"firefox","Ublock"),"Firefox, Ublock"))
    drawBoxes(boxes,'Subsequent Loads 85% Visual Completion for '+regionToCity[l],ylimit=10000)
    
# These graphs show the same metric, but for subsequent page loads on the same
# domain. So the browser already has a connection open when the user clicks an
# internal link or similar.Figures are broken down by the browser used and
# whether Ublock was enabled.
